org.cooperari.core

Class COperation<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.cooperari.core.COperation<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - Type for operation result. It is usually parameterized as Void.
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CustomYieldPointOperation, DataOperation, HotspotOperation, MonitorOperation, ThreadOperation, ThreadRunnerOperation

    public abstract class COperation<T>
extends Object
    Base class for cooperative operations.

    Subclasses should override when necessary the following methods:

    • getState(), if the operation is subject to blocking;
    • execute(), if the operation has associated actions -- operations that merely introduce yield points before proceeding to application code should not need to;
    • getResult(), if the operation has an associated result, when T is not Void;
    • and, finally, getAbortOperation() if the operation requires cleanup actions on thread death.

    The _arguments field is intentionally protected, and forms the base for the implementations of equals(Object) as hashCode() --both of which play an important role in program state representation/abstraction -- as well as toString() in this class. These three methods cannot be overridden by subclasses (they are final).

    Since:
    0.2

      • getState

        public CThreadState getState()
        Get operation state. This method can be called by ANY thread. The default implementation signals the thread as ready.
        Returns:
        CThreadState.CREADY

      • execute

        public void execute()
        Execute the operation. The method is guaranteed to run within the cooperative thread the operation associates to. The default operation does nothing.

      • getResult

        public T getResult()
        Get operation result. The method is guaranteed to run within the cooperative thread the operation associates to.
        Returns:
        The default result is null

      • getAbortOperation

        public COperation<?> getAbortOperation()
        Get abort operation. The abort operation aids the thread death procedure, by performing any necessary prior actions to the actual "death sequence". The method should be overridden when abrupt termination requires a prior operation to do some cleanup.
        Returns:
        A COperation object. The base implementation returns a no-op abort action that allows thread death to proceed immediately.

      • getStage

        public int getStage()
        Get yield point stage for this operation. The base implementation returns 0.
        Returns:
        The stage for the yield point this operation relates to.
        See Also:
        CThreadLocation
